    },
    {
        "Wikh-i-Zalmayan": "weekh zalmian"
    },
    {
        " , a progressive and leftist organization. He studied at the College of Law and Political Science at Kabul University from 1951 to 1953. In 1953 Karmal was arrested because of his student union activities, but was released three years later in 1956 in an amnesty by ": null
    },
    {
        "Muhammad Daoud Khan": "muhammad daoud khan"
    },
    {
        ". Shortly after, in 1957, Karmal found work as an English and German translator, before quitting and leaving for military training. Karmal graduated from the College of Law and Political Science in 1960, and in 1961, he found work as an employee in the Compilation and Translation Department of the ": null
    },
    {
        "Ministry of Education": "ministry of education"
    },
    {
        ". From 1961 to 1963 he worked in the ": null
    },
    {
        "Ministry of Planning": "ministry of planning"
    },
    {
        ". When his mother died, Karmal left with his maternal aunt to live somewhere else. His father disowned him because of his leftist views. Karmal was involved in much ": null
    },
    {
        "debauchery": ":wikt:debauchery"
    },
    {
