        ", respectively. The appointment of Amin, Karmal and Watanjar led to splits within the Council of Ministers: the Khalqists answered to Amin; Karmal led the civilian Parchamites; and the military officers were answerable to Watanjar . The first conflict arose when the Khalqists wanted to give PDPA Central Committee membership to military officers who had participated in the ": null
    },
